cyclone.name: ZETA
cyclone.current_location: about 255 mi SSE of the western tip of Cuba
cyclone.trajectory: Forecast to turn west-northwest, cross or skirt the Yucatan Channel late Monday, enter the southern Gulf Tuesday, then accelerate north-northeast toward the northern Gulf Coast and eventually curve across the Southeast toward the Mid-Atlantic late Thursday-Friday.

weather_observation.watch_coast: Pinar del Rio province, western Cuba
weather_observation.impacted_coast: Western Cuba, northeast Yucatan Peninsula, northern Gulf Coast from eastern Texas to the Florida Panhandle and eventually inland across the Southeast U.S.
weather_observation.wind: Breezy conditions possible late week with gusts 20–30 mph as remnants pass south of the port.
weather_observation.storm_surge: None anticipated for Baltimore due to inland track and weak intensity by arrival.
weather_observation.rainfall: 1–2 inches of rain possible late Thursday into Friday with locally higher amounts, which could cause ponding on docks and roadways.
weather_observation.other_hazards: Minor river/stream rises and potential scheduling delays for truck and rail connections.
